# Stack Cross-Layer Conventions

## Shared Principles

- Apply SOLID principles (especially SRP and DIP) and keep business logic separate from orchestration and technical adapters.
- Keep a single responsibility per class, module, and component.
- Avoid `any`; explicitly type public input/output contracts.
- Prefer readable, intention-revealing code.

## Architecture and Dependencies

- In both frontend and backend layers, do not mix business logic with integration concerns (UI, HTTP, DB, external APIs).
- Centralize external integrations in dedicated services/adapters.
- Favor dependency injection to improve testability and change resilience.

## Cross-Layer Testing

- Use Vitest for all tests.
- Keep tests isolated and deterministic (reset mocks in `beforeEach`).
- Prefer behavior-focused tests over implementation-detail tests.
- Use a `tests/` folder when aligned with package/app conventions.

## Quality and Verification

- Before integration, run lint/format/tests for the impacted package.
- If a conflict appears between this cross-layer rule and a specialized rule, the specialized frontend/backend rule takes precedence.
